# Testing And Verification

- Read nearby tests before adding or changing tests. Match local helpers, fixtures, naming, and assertion style.
- Test intent and regressions, not just implementation details.
- Work from the package you changed where practical. Use narrow checks first, then broaden when shared contracts or risky behavior changed.
- Backend and node packages commonly use Jest; frontend packages commonly use Vitest; E2E uses Playwright under `packages/testing/playwright`.
- For changed API contracts, verify both producer and consumer packages when feasible.
- For Playwright changes, read `packages/testing/playwright/AGENTS.md` and run janitor checks for new or modified tests.
- Never report "tests pass" unless you ran them. Name exactly what was run and what was skipped.
